						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the hind wall of the Rāmaliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is a very badly damaged inscription. It mentions Rāyachūra and refers to Keṁḍada (dēva). Probably the record registered a grant the details of which are lost.</p>						

						<p>In the date portion it mentions the cyclic year Vyaya, Pushya, Śu (3) Friday. The given details here are insufficient for verification for the cyclic year Vyaya occurred twice during this century <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Śaka 1343 (1421-22 A.D.) and Śaka 1403 (1481-82 A.D.).</p>						

						</summary>
